A living archive for procedural literacy, system navigation, and real‑world legal survival.

The Legal Calculus Educational System is a multi‑layer learning architecture built from real artifacts, real filings, and real system behavior.
It is not a “course.”
It is a procedural‑literacy engine designed to help ordinary people survive and document legal processes.

This repo is the archive, the classroom, and the field guide.

---

🧭 System Map (LC • LCA • FG • FGA • JC • LCa)

LC — Legal Calculus (Modules 1–119)

Core teaching system: philosophy, structure, assignments, visuals, doctrine, strategy.

LCA — Legal Calculus Advanced

Deep dives: appellate posture, complex motions, sanctions, evidentiary structure.

FG — Field Guide (FG‑1…FG‑1000)

Quick‑reference micro‑modules: checklists, forms, one‑page tactics, emergency steps.

FGA — Field Guide Advanced

Expert‑level checklists: arbitration, evidentiary nuance, spoliation, edge‑case tactics.

JC — Judicial Calculus

How courts actually behave: discretion patterns, denial logic, doctrine deflection.

LCa — Lawyer Calculus

Practitioner workflows: risk controls, clinic teaching, proposed‑order discipline.

Mental Model

- FG / FGA → Do it now
• LC / LCA → Learn why + do it right
• JC / LCa → Anticipate the system

