🧩 TNRPESC — The 7‑Point Pre‑File Check

Before filing anything, run this sequence:

1. Tone
2. Narrative
3. Relief (Proposed Order)
4. Procedure / Rule
5. Evidence (pinpoints)
6. Service & /s/ signature
7. Citations + TOA (email to yourself for timestamped diligence)

This is the minimum viable discipline for survivable filings.

---

⚠️ Known Pitfalls (Read Before Filing)

- No Proposed Order → judge says “nothing to rule” → strike
• Wrong summons → service defect → dismissal
• Formatting errors → clerk rejection
• Late by mail → move for equivalent extension (attach envelope)
• Repeat filings w/o stating what’s new → vexatious‑litigant risk

