🧰 Choose Your Mode

The repo supports three primary modes of use.

---

1. 🚨 Crisis Mode (Pro Se in a Hurry)
2. Open the FG Index → choose the micro‑module that matches your emergency
3. Pull the matching template → fill → /s/ sign → export to locked PDF
4. Add a one‑line Proposed Order
5. Validate citations → generate TOA → email to yourself
6. File (ECF if allowed; else USPS Certified + RRR; invoke Mailbox Rule)
7. If time: skim the paired LC module (e.g., Winter standard, Format is Force)
8. Archive in /packets/ with docket reference

Crisis Shortcuts

- Delay traps → document + move for extension (Rule 6(b))
• Vexatious shield → state goal + what’s new; incorporate exhibits by reference

---

1. 🧑‍🏫 Educator / Clinic Mode
- Start from Master Field Guide v1.0 for syllabus framing
• Assign LC modules (1–119)
• Use FG/FGA for practicum and simulations
• Use JC to teach judicial behavior (discretion vs. law)
• Use LCa for practitioner labs (risk controls, proposed‑order discipline)
• Push improvements back into /field-guide/ as new FG entries

---

1. 🧪 Second‑Opinion Mode (Litigant or Lawyer)

8‑Step Pass

1. State the goal
2. Read the docket
3. Pull FG micro‑modules
4. Open paired LC/LCA modules
5. Validate cites → TOA → email
6. Attach Proposed Order
7. COS + filing plan
8. Archive to /packets/

Special Situations

- Arbitration → consult FGA + LCA
• Judicial behavior issues → cite JC modules

